OA Transportation Director, Tony Quaranta, spoke with Annie Flaherty about our plans for social distancing on a school bus. Thanks for having us as your last story at WBNG 12 News, Annie! Best wishes as you move on with your career.

Please notify the OA Transportation office ASAP at 607-687-7305 if:
---Your child(ren) needs transportation to/from a location other than your home address
--- You have siblings that have different start/end times and you want them to ride together

Otherwise, routes will be built based on your home address and student pick-up/drop-off will be based on their individual start/end times.

Please also remember that students must travel to and from school on the same bus, every day of the week.

Owego Elementary School PTO, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group

#OACommunity #OAPride #OATradition

If your child(ren) needs transportation to/from a location other than your home address, please notify the Transportation office ASAP at 607-687-7305. Questions can always be emailed to dateline@oacsd.org or you can contact your school building directly.

***Please Note: OACSD does not respond to comments or questions on Facebook. Please contact us directly by phone or email.***

Congratulations to the Owego Free Academy Class of 2020. The 147th Annual Commencement was divided into 5 different ceremonies held on Friday, June 26 and Sunday, June 28 in the Christy J. Valvo Stadium.

Footage from the 5 separate ceremonies and pre-recorded speeches have been compiled into one 41 minute long video. You can watch it here: https://youtu.be/XKgUPAmowbI

A music video featuring footage from graduation was created to go along with the song ‚ÄúHere‚Äôs To You‚Äù by Abby Bannon, who gave permission to use her song in our videos. You can watch it here: https://youtu.be/6amafiX_ZFU

Each ceremony has their own video from the live stream broadcast that can be seen on our YouTube Channel here: https://www.youtube.com/user/OwegoYouSchools

Some other OFA Class of 2020 videos and photo albums you may have missed:

Car Parade Video: https://youtu.be/3Dh6118k1yw

Cap and Gown Handout Celebration Video: https://youtu.be/bHauf4h9Tvg

OA Photo Albums (Graduation Ceremonies, Car Parade, Senior Spotlights and more): https://www.oacsd.org/OAPhotos1.aspx

OFA GRADUATION CEREMONIES #4 AND #5 POSTPONED TO SUNDAY

Due to the weather forecasted for today, Saturday, June 27 the OFA graduation ceremonies #4 and #5 (9am & 10am) have been postponed to tomorrow, Sunday, June 28 at 9am and 10am. The ceremonies will be streamed live on the OACSD YouTube Channel here: https://www.youtube.com/user/OwegoYouSchools

Thank you for your continued flexibility, patience and understanding.

Owego Free Academy held 3 ceremonies on Friday night at 6, 7 and 8pm that were streamed and can be viewed on the YouTube Channel.

WEBO - Your Hometown Station will broadcast a pre-recorded version of graduation today, Saturday, June 27 at Noon. This will feature all speeches by students and administration and every graduates name. If you miss the broadcast at noon, it will be available on the WEBO website: www.myhometowntoday.com after it airs.

Owego Apalachin Musicals and Plays
June 22 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

During this time of remote learning, we want to let our students know that we are always here for you!

The song ‚ÄúAin‚Äôt No Mountain High Enough‚Äù was written by Nickolas Ashford and Valerie Simpson in 1966, inspired by a walk through Central Park and their ambition to become a part of Motown Records. It was originally recorded by Marvin Gaye and Tammi Terrell.

Besides shaping the sound of Motown in the 1960‚Äôs, Marvin Gaye was equally important in the fight for racial equality. His top album, ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs Going On‚Äù, is just as relevant now as when it was released in 1971.

Check out the Motown Records website for more information on Marvin Gaye, Tammi Terrell, and other artists from the 1960‚Äôs through today.

post_text:
Voters in the Owego Apalachin Central School District on Tuesday, June 16 voted to approve the district‚Äôs proposed 2020-2021 school budget of $47,717,978.

The budget had a decrease of 0.09 percent, and a tax levy increase of 1.82 percent.

The final vote was:
Yes: 1,754
No: 640

In a second proposition, voters approved the purchase of 5 school buses and 1 suburban by the following count:
Yes: 1,603
No: 789

Three Board of Education Candidates elected for three seats were:
Stacey Riegel, Kathie Rollison, and Daniel Whippo

Voters approved the additional taxpayer funding for the Apalachin Public Library
Yes: 1,513
No: 867

#OACommunity #OAPride #OATradition

REMINDER

The district will hold its Official Public Budget Hearing virtually tonight, Tuesday, May 26th at 6:00PM via Live Stream on our YouTube Channel here: https://youtu.be/ipQf4aLbflU

Questions about the proposed budget can be sent in using the Chat feature on the Live YouTube Feed, or by emailing dateline@oacsd.org.

You can view 2020-2021 budget information, including the digital version of our budget newsletter here: https://www.oacsd.org/2020-2021BudgetInfo.aspx (Printed copies will be coming in the mail.)

Absentee Ballots are being mailed to registered voters and should begin to arrive via USPS over the next week. Voting and absentee ballot questions can be emailed to vote@oacsd.org

Other district questions, please call (607) 687-7307 x7777

*Reminder the school district does not reply to Facebook posts. Please contact the district directly using one of the methods above if you have a question.*

2020 CENSUS REMINDER

The 2020 Census counts every person living in the United States and five U.S. territories. In mid-March, homes across the country began receiving invitations to complete the 2020 Census. You should respond for your home in one of three ways: online, by phone, or by mail.

It only takes 10 minutes to support kids for the next 10 years! The census informs where hundreds of billions in funding will go each year for things like education, healthcare and programs that touch us all. Call, return your form by mail, or go online to www.2020Census.gov.

According to Tioga Counts 2020 as of May 6th - Tioga County was #2 in New York State with 62% responding.

#OACommunity #OAPride #OATogether

post_text:
The 2020 Regional Emerging Artists Show and Competition was scheduled to be on display in the Oakdale Mall, but was canceled due to the COVID-19 pandemic closing the mall. Unfortunately, many students, parents and other visitors were unable to view this wonderful show. Three Owego Free Academy students earned awards for their submissions.

Congratulations to Jennifer Scott and Nicole Holt for taking 1st Place in their categories and to Olivia Holt for earning Best of Show for her Beethoven birthday tribute!

More OFA art galleries can be found here: https://www.oacsd.org/OwegoApalachinArtDepartment.aspx

#OAisYOU #OACommunity #OAPride #OATradition

OFA Yearbook, Owego Elementary School PTO, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group, OA Music Boosters, OFA Sports Booster Club

post_text:
GAME ON FOR OA ONLINE TOURNAMENT #2

Calling all OACSD students. Check out the attached details on the upcoming OA online gaming tournament. Mrs. Melby and the OFA gaming club have created another Super Smash Bros. Ultimate online tournament on the Nintendo Switch, this time playing doubles. The 2 vs. 2 Teams will be randomly created on the day of the tournament.

Register by May 14th for the tournament running Friday, May 15th and Saturday, May 16th.

Gaming Club is also curious about what online games you might be interested in playing with other OA students. The following link is for a quick survey that will help them plan their next online gaming activity:

https://owegoit.com/gamingsurvey

Contact Mrs. Melby (melbyb@oacsd.org) with any questions about the survey or the tournament.

(Flyer is also located in virtual backpack tile for each school building on district app.)

#OACommunity #OAPride #OATogether

Owego Elementary School PTO, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group, OFA Sports Booster Club, OA Music Boosters, OFA Yearbook

post_text:
Looking for some fun science experiments to try at home?

Retired OA teacher, Mr. Lewis, created 5 'Air Pressure' experiment videos using items you might have around the house.

Since retiring a few years back, Mr. Lewis has regularly visited students at Apalachin and Owego Elementary Schools to conduct science experiments. He has been missing the interactions with students and teachers and wanted to attempt some virtual experiments with them.

Have some fun and give them a try. Share your pictures and videos with us by using the google form link on the website.

https://www.oacsd.org/SciencewithMrLewis.aspx

#OASTEAM #OACommunity #OAPride #OATogether

Owego Elementary School, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group

shared_text:
Tioga Arts Council
April 17 at 2:43 PM ¬∑

SPECIAL "Square Awareness" announcement.

Each year for artfully SQUARED, we receive an incredible amount of donated artwork from people of all ages and skill levels in our community. Because we received such wonderful support, we wanted to give back to our community during COVID19.

Featured here are over 80 pieces of artwork ‚Äì primarily created by Owego Free Academy Students and their teacher, Susan Camin ‚Äì that we delivered to the residents at Riverview Manor Rehabilitation & Nursing this afternoon. It is our hope that these works of art brighten walls of this facility and bring joy to its residents.

In times like these, we hope this artwork will nourish the spirit of those at Riverview Manor Rehabilitation & Nursing.

Be safe, be well, and ‚Äì if possible ‚Äì be creative.

PS: We will still have artfully SQUARED pieces displayed on social media and available for a $20 donation. Stay tuned for next week, we have a special Monster Adoption Drive.

The Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic continues to have wide-ranging impacts. If your family is experiencing a financial impact during these difficult times, there could be benefits available to you.

Sign up for free and reduced school meals by applying online at https://www.myschoolapps.com/. Free and reduced meals would be available for your child(ren) for the remainder of the school year and 30 business days into next school year.

If you are a family that is in need of extra assistance you can also apply for SNAP benefits at https://www.ny.gov/services/apply-snap. The Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) issues electronic benefits that can be used like cash to purchase food at stores.

The Tioga County Chamber of Commerce Community Awards were presented at the Chamber‚Äôs Annual Dinner on Thursday, February 13, 2020 at the Terra Cotta Owego Banquet Center. Special recognition is given to those Chamber Members who have made a significant contribution to the community and help promote the Chamber‚Äôs mission to support and promote the economic and civic well-being of Tioga County. Award winners were selected by committee and voted on by the Chamber‚Äôs Board of Directors.

The 2020 Award recipients were:

Community Impact Award: Owego Apalachin Central School District

Legacy Award: Pat Hansen, Hand of Man

Business of the Year: The 1867 Parkview Inn & Dugan House Restaurant

A great day for OFA senior Jasper Corson as he signed an agreement with Lockheed Martin of Owego for a full-time job after graduation.

Jasper has been working at Lockheed Martin through a co-op over the past year. He has been spending half of his school day taking courses at OFA and the other half working at the Owego Lockheed Martin site.

As OA Superintendent Green stated, "Today‚Äôs celebration highlights how heading directly to a career opportunity right out of high school can provide current and future opportunities. Our goal as a school district is to provide all of our students with options for future success through careers or college."

Jasper is one of five OFA students participating in a co-op with Lockheed Martin. We also have several other students participating in co-op experiences with other local businesses.

#OACommunity #OAPride #OATradition

Project STEAM 21, Owego Elementary School PTO, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group, OFA Sports Booster Club

AES and OES 3rd - 5th grade teachers and their colleagues spent the week working with a Staff Developer from the The Teachers College Reading and Writing Project (TCRWP) at a Home Grown Reading Institute. The Teachers College is part of Columbia University.

For the past few years, the TCRWP staff have joined with districts and schools to plan and lead institutes across the country. Home Grown Institutes are one of the most effective ways to galvanize the Reading & Writing Project‚Äôs work across a school or district.

The 4 day on-site institute has been tailored to help our OA educators focus on specific areas of need, based on assessments, prior knowledge, and district goals.

Read more about it here:
https://www.oacsd.org/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=5IUAYY&dasi=3YYB

Owego Elementary School PTO, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group

The OA Garden Club Summer Enrichment Camp at Apalachin Elementary School teamed up with Cornell Cooperative Extension of Tioga County to build a farm stand for AES produce. With the kids working hard this summer in the AES Learning Garden, they wanted to be ready for when produce begins to grow. Pictured is Tanner from OES and Caleb from AES with Barb Neal from Cornell Cooperative Extension. Mr. ‚ÄúO‚Äù is also pictured, as he is the grandfather of Caleb and retired AES Librarian. The farm stand is located in front of AES and will hold the extra produce from the AES Learning Garden. The community is welcome to check the farm stand periodically to see if there is any extra produce available for FREE and can always donate any extra produce to share from their home gardens.

#OACommunity #OAPride #OASummerEnrichment

The OACSD I.T. Department started iPAD handouts today, Wednesday, August 7th. They will be in the OAMS lobby until 3:30pm today. Tomorrow, Thursday, August 8th they will be in the OAMS Lobby from 9:00 to 11:30am and 1:00 to 3:30pm.

****The I.T. Department has added Tuesday, August 13th and Wednesday, August 14th from 4:30 to 7:30pm as other possible pick-up options.****

These handout times are only for students in 7th, 8th, 10th, 11th and 12th grade. A student or parent can pick-up the device during these open times.

Anyone not able to pick-up their iPAD during these handout times will get it on the first day of school just like they have in the past.

6th and 9th grade students will be given their iPADS during their orientation night. Any student not attending orientation would get their iPAD on the first day of school.

6th Grade Orientation is Thursday, August 29th at 6:00pm

9th Grade Orientation is Wednesday, August 28th at 6:30pm

Any questions contact the school directly at (607) 687-7301 ext. 1070

The Tioga County Sheriff's Office conducted a training exercise this morning on the OA campus to help prepare the SWAT team for a school emergency situation.

The simulation was a bus hostage crisis, where the team trained on one of our out of commission buses that will soon be scrapped. The Campville Fire Dept will also use this bus for an upcoming training scenario.

We are extremely grateful for all of our first responders. We understand the importance of their training exercises and are thankful to be able to work with them.

See the news stories below for more:

WBNG 12 News -
https://wbng.com/news/featured-reports/2019/07/13/tioga-county-sheriffs-office-holds-swat-training-simulation/

Spectrum News Southern Tier -

post_text: ICYMI: In honor of World No Tobacco Day 5/31/19, Owego Reality Check youth conducted a peer education event. Reality Check and SADD Club members hung hundreds of post-it notes with the words Target, Replacement, 13, and various kid friendly flavors on the library windows at Owego Free Academy. Reality Check youth educated their peers during lunch periods on the deceptive marketing tactics of Big Tobacco companies. Students participated in a flavor poll activity proving how kid friendly flavors target youth. The conclusion of the World No Tobacco Day event was at the Binghamton Rumble Ponies game where Owego and Windsor Reality Check youth continued to educate community members. See more pictures here: https://www.oacsd.org/OAPhotos.aspx

OA Schools
June 11, 2019 at 1:04 PM ¬∑

The OA Music Department and OA Art Department are collaboratively hosting a "Night of the Arts" on Tuesday, June 18th from 4:00 to 8:00 pm. Apalachin Elementary School and Owego Apalachin Middle School will both be hosting different performances as part of this incredible event. We would like to invite the entire Owego Apalachin community to this FREE celebration of the Arts, and to support the students involved.

Music Performances in the OA Theater will begin at 4:00 pm. Different OA Art pieces on display in the Art Show Winner‚Äôs Circle. Black light painting workshops at 4:00 pm and 5:00 pm at OAMS.

Apalachin Elementary will showcase the 3rd grade musical starting at 6:00pm, followed by the 4th/5th grade chorus as well as an African drum and dance featuring current AES music students and any alumni who have an interest in participating.

Special thanks to OA Music Boosters, Owego Apalachin Bands, Owego Free Academy Choirs, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group, Owego Elementary School PTO and the OA Art Department.

Check out the flyer for specific details:

American Dairy Association North East added 29 new photos to the album: NY Thursdays Strong Haven Farm Tour ‚Äî at Stronghaven Farm LLC.
June 13, 2019 ¬∑ Barton, NY ¬∑

The Owego Apalachin Central School District, in partnership with the American Dairy Association North East, participated in a fun promotional program to highlight food from local New York State Farms. Once a month the district does "New York Thursdays" where the district offers a menu of locally sourced milk, dairy products and other foods from New York State Farms.

Owego Elementary School won the NY Thursdays contest and was awarded with a Dairy Farm tour for 30 students of Strong Haven Farm in Barton, N.Y. The students had the opportunity to watch cows being milked, walk through the barns, and pet and feed a calf!

We would like to invite the entire Owego Apalachin community to this FREE celebration of the Arts, and to support the students involved.

Music Performances in the OA Theater will begin at 4:00 pm. Different OA Art pieces on display in the Art Show Winner‚Äôs Circle. Black light painting workshops at 4:00 pm and 5:00 pm at OAMS.

Apalachin Elementary will showcase the 3rd grade musical starting at 6:00pm, followed by the 4th/5th grade chorus as well as an African drum and dance featuring current AES music students and any alumni who have an interest in participating.

Special thanks to OA Music Boosters, Owego Apalachin Bands, Owego Free Academy Choirs, Apalachin Elementary School Parent Group, Owego Elementary School PTO and the OA Art Department.

Check out the flyer for specific details:

REMINDER: The Board of Education will hold a Public Budget Workshop tonight, Tuesday, May 28, 2019. This will begin at 6:00 P.M. in the BOE room at the District Office (5 Sheldon Guile Blvd. Owego). At this meeting, the Board of Education will take into consideration the next steps for the 2019-2020 school budget. Those could include a re-vote on the current budget, a re-vote on a revised budget, or going directly to a contingency budget. A re-vote would occur on the statewide re-vote date of June 18, 2019. District information is always available on our website, www.oacsd.org.

The Board of Education will have a regular meeting on Thursday, May 30th at 7:00 P.M.

Three Owego Apalachin Central School District Mathalon teams competed today in the Tioga County Coalition For Better Schools 2018-2019 Mathalon competition at Spencer Van Etten Middle School.

A 5th Grade Team from Apalachin Elementary School, coached by Mrs. Chrysler and Mrs. Jerge, was made up of: Sam Beyer, Jaelyn Chrysler, Joey Gaurnier, Connor Kotski, Leah Teeter and Wyatt Tirinato-Snow.

A 5th Grade Team from Owego Elementary School, coached by Mr. McCloe, was made up of: Myla Yartz, Taylor Signs, Gabriella Boehme, Gavin Heath, Tatum Kowalski and Madison Kinney.

A 6th Grade Team from Owego Apalachin Middle School, coached by Mrs. Monforte, was made up of: Ruben Lemmon, Ryan Barnes, Nora Schuyler, Kaelyn Katchuk, Sullivan O'Donnell, Madison McEvoy and Matt Higgins.

The AES team finished in 2nd place in the 5th grade division and the OAMS team took 1st place in the 6th grade division.

Wonderful job done by all the kids and teachers!

post_text: Owego Elementary School students participated in a March Madness Book Reading Challenge. If they reached their goal of 5,000 books during the month of March, Mr. Francisco, OES Principal, would receive a pie to the face. The students were also able to vote for a teacher or staff member to join in the fun! The OES students met their goal of 5,000 books and then some. They ended up reading 19,732 books during the March Madness Reading Challenge. The entire building celebrated their amazing accomplishment with not just 2 pies, but 6 since they read so many books.

Fred Akshar
March 21, 2019 at 4:01 PM ¬∑

Was happy to start the morning in Apalachin Elementary School to talk to students about the importance of Agriculture. Thank you to our partners at Cornell Cooperative Extension-Broome County and Broome-Tioga BOCES for this partnership. Our Ag in the classroom program started in 5 school district and has grown today to 13. We look forward to expanding into more schools next year and teaching our children about the importance of agriculture. A special thanks to OA Schools‚Äôs Superintendent Corey Green who is one of our original partners and has never wavered from his commitment to the group and CCE Broome County‚Äôs Brian Aukema for his dedication to educating our community.

post_text:
OFA Girls and Boys Basketball teams will play for the Section 4 Class B Title today, Saturday, March 2nd.

OFA Girls (19-1) and ranked 5th in the state by the New York State Sports Writers Association, will play Norwich (21-1) and ranked 4th in the state. The girls only loss on the season was to Norwich(74-39) in the STAC Championship game on February 15th.

Girls game is at 5pm.

OFA Boys (18-3) honorable mention by the New York State Sports Writers Association, will play Seton Catholic (19-3) and ranked 16th in the state. The boys will be looking to avenge their (60-43) STAC Championship loss to Seton.

Boys game is at 7pm.

Both games are being played at the Broome County Floyd L Maines Arena. Admission is $7 for regular tickets and $5 for Senior Citizens.

Games will also be live video streamed on the NFHS Network (with a paid subscription that can be canceled at any time).

To find out more or watch, go here: https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/schools/owego-free-academy-owego-ny

post_text: Parents of OFA Seniors - it is NOT too late to order a Parent Recognition Ad to honor your student in the Yearbook! The deadline for submitting an ad to Jostens is Feb. 14, but you can submit pictures and text to Ms. Starks at starksk@oacsd.org through March. Here is the flyer with the ad prices and ordering info on it. Feel free to contact Ms. Starks with any questions.

post_text:
The Possibilities are a band of 6th Graders from the Owego Apalachin Middle School. This performance was filmed by the students at Windsor Central School District at the 9th Annual KORT Festival. Special thanks to Joel Carle and the students at Windsor High School. "Lose Yourself" was originally performed by Eminem. Third verse of this performance was written by Gianna Paolucci.

(More videos can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqF0FB7BWpwomOmd4-tpb9A/featured)

https://youtu.be/5t2e5tAEtSk
